The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Dravid tops averages

New Delhi: Virender Sehwag emerged the highest run-getter as India dominated the statistical charts, sweeping the batting and bowling honours in the two-Test series against South Africa. 

Sehwag amassed 262 runs at an average of 87.33, though it was Rahul Dravid who topped the batting averages with 90.50 compiling 181 runs.Harbhajan Singh stood out among the bowlers with an impressive haul of 13 wickets taken at an average of 23.61. 

The other Indian top order batsmen, who had fared dismally against Australia, once again failed to get the big scores. Though Sourav Ganguly did marginally better (48.50), Sachin Tendulkar (27.50) and V.V.S. Laxman (23.50) continued to disappoint. (PTI) 

